*[.md-style.rb, line 1 at r1](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/website/16#-Ka-RIBi-okZAiCXlEie:-Ka-RIBi-okZAiCXlEif:bqspegq) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/website/blob/6c573b187a9af3a91129c1e4a218fee1236ff23d/.md-style.rb#L1)):*
> ```Ruby
> all
> ```

Can we sort the rules in ascending order? Regardless of whether they're excluded or configured. Makes going through them together with https://github.com/mivok/markdownlint/blob/master/docs/RULES.md easier.

---

*[toktok/spec.md, line 8 at r1](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/website/16#-Ka-V0g6Gey4NTA7GRMa:-Ka-V0g6Gey4NTA7GRMb:b-t2ufii) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/website/blob/6c573b187a9af3a91129c1e4a218fee1236ff23d/toktok/spec.md#L8)):*
> ```Markdown
> ---
> 
> *   The line below will tell kramdown to generate the ToC on this line.
> ```

You can replace `*` with `-` so it matches the other lists. It only has to be a list marker. You can even make it `1.` for a numbered list.
